Route-based VPN Gateway uses dynamic routing to direct traffic between networks.

It supports protocols like BGP (Border Gateway Protocol) for automatic route updates.

For example, traffic is routed based on routing tables instead of static policies.

A real-life use case is large enterprises with complex network architectures.

Another example is multi-site connectivity where routes change dynamically.

Route-based VPNs provide flexibility, scalability, and advanced routing capabilities.
